text: Gaienhofen is a municipality in the district of Konstanz in Baden-Württemberg in Germany. Gaienhofen has two museums: the Hermann-Hesse-Höri-Museum and Otto-Dix-Haus. == History == The municipality has four villages: Gaienhofen, Gundholzen, Hemmenhofen and Horn. == Twin towns == Gaienhofen is twinned with: * Saint-Georges-de-Didonne, France * Balatonföldvár, Hungary == References == == Other websites == * Official website * Otto-Dix-Haus * Hermann-Hesse-Höri- Museum * Hermann-Hesse-Haus Category:Konstanz (district)
